{
    "publish_date": "2013-04-07T18:39:21.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT12M5S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "DR. JAMES GRIME: So Zeno&#39;s\nparadox is a problem that&#39;s", 
            "dur": "2.32", 
            "start": "0.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "not just of interest to\nmathematicians, like myself.", 
            "dur": "2.81", 
            "start": "2.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But it&#39;s also of interest to\nphysicists and philosophers.", 
            "dur": "4.02", 
            "start": "5.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it has been for thousands\nof years.", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "9.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So Zeno was a Greek\nphilosopher.", 
            "dur": "2.82", 
            "start": "11.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He lived 2,500 years ago.", 
            "dur": "3.31", 
            "start": "14.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And he came up with a\nlist of paradoxes.", 
            "dur": "3.35", 
            "start": "17.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There&#39;s about nine of\nthese paradoxes.", 
            "dur": "2.1", 
            "start": "21.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The ones I want to talk about,\nthough, are kind of similar.", 
            "dur": "4.06", 
            "start": "23.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The first one, though, I love,\nbecause there&#39;s a nice little", 
            "dur": "3.43", 
            "start": "27.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "story with it.", 
            "dur": "0.83", 
            "start": "30.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the first one is called\nAchilles and the Tortoise.", 
            "dur": "3.27", 
            "start": "31.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You&#39;ve got Achilles and the\ntortoise in a race.", 
            "dur": "3.05", 
            "start": "34.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, the tortoise is\nslower, of course.", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "37.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So he&#39;s given a head start.", 
            "dur": "1.44", 
            "start": "40.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He&#39;s got a 100 meter\nhead start.", 
            "dur": "2.85", 
            "start": "41.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then they start the race.", 
            "dur": "1.7", 
            "start": "44.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, Achilles sprints 100\nmeters, and he catches up to", 
            "dur": "4.25", 
            "start": "46.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "where the tortoise was.", 
            "dur": "2.23", 
            "start": "50.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But in that time, the tortoise\nhas moved on.", 
            "dur": "3.4", 
            "start": "52.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He&#39;s moved on 10 meters.", 
            "dur": "1.83", 
            "start": "55.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So Achilles now has to sprint\nto catch up with", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "57.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the tortoise, again.", 
            "dur": "1.03", 
            "start": "60.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So he sprints another 10 meters,\nand he catches up to", 
            "dur": "2.85", 
            "start": "61.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "where the tortoise was.", 
            "dur": "1.93", 
            "start": "64.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, since that time,\nthe tortoise has", 
            "dur": "1.68", 
            "start": "66.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "moved on another meter.", 
            "dur": "2.39", 
            "start": "68.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So Achilles has to sprint\nto catch up to where", 
            "dur": "2.24", 
            "start": "70.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the tortoise was.", 
            "dur": "1.15", 
            "start": "72.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this keeps happening\nover and over again.", 
            "dur": "2.81", 
            "start": "74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the paradox is does Achilles\never catch up with", 
            "dur": "3.98", 
            "start": "76.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the tortoise?", 
            "dur": "1.58", 
            "start": "80.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that&#39;s insane.", 
            "dur": "3.21", 
            "start": "82.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And obviously, he must do.", 
            "dur": "2.83", 
            "start": "85.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We all live in the real world.", 
            "dur": "1.76", 
            "start": "88.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He must catch up with\nthe tortoise.", 
            "dur": "2.02", 
            "start": "90.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Another of these paradoxes is\nbasically the same, but it&#39;s a", 
            "dur": "4.3", 
            "start": "92.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "bit simpler.", 
            "dur": "1.05", 
            "start": "96.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m holding my hands\napart like that.", 
            "dur": "2.71", 
            "start": "97.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, I&#39;m going to keep\nmy left hand still.", 
            "dur": "2.625", 
            "start": "100.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m going to move my right hand\ntowards my left hand so", 
            "dur": "2.975", 
            "start": "102.875"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that they clap.", 
            "dur": "1.86", 
            "start": "105.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, when I do that--", 
            "dur": "1.86", 
            "start": "107.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "actually, you can think of it\nlike I&#39;m halving the distance.", 
            "dur": "3.43", 
            "start": "109.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I then halve the distance\nagain and then halve the", 
            "dur": "2.61", 
            "start": "113"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "distance again and again\nand again and again.", 
            "dur": "2.68", 
            "start": "115.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I halve the distance an\ninfinite number of times,", 
            "dur": "3.54", 
            "start": "118.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "infinitely many times.", 
            "dur": "1.81", 
            "start": "121.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So does that mean my\nhands never clap?", 
            "dur": "3.065", 
            "start": "123.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Is there some sort of\nforce field here", 
            "dur": "2.334", 
            "start": "126.705"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "stopping my hands meeting?", 
            "dur": "1.891", 
            "start": "129.039"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, obviously, they do.", 
            "dur": "3.08", 
            "start": "130.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is the paradox.", 
            "dur": "1.12", 
            "start": "134.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So what&#39;s going on here?", 
            "dur": "1.64", 
            "start": "135.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How can an infinite\nprocess end?", 
            "dur": "4.55", 
            "start": "136.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What&#39;s going on?", 
            "dur": "0.63", 
            "start": "141.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this is part of\nZeno&#39;s paradoxes.", 
            "dur": "3.64", 
            "start": "141.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I want to give you the\nmathematician&#39;s point of view", 
            "dur": "2.05", 
            "start": "145.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for this, because, well, some\nsay that the mathematicians", 
            "dur": "3.65", 
            "start": "147.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "have sorted this out.", 
            "dur": "2.35", 
            "start": "151.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s say I start with my\nhands 2 meters apart.", 
            "dur": "4.38", 
            "start": "153.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then I&#39;m going to\njoin them together.", 
            "dur": "1.94", 
            "start": "158.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So they start 2 meters apart,\nand then I halve the distance.", 
            "dur": "4.24", 
            "start": "159.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I&#39;ve traveled 1 meter.", 
            "dur": "1.93", 
            "start": "164.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I then halve the distance again,\nso we&#39;ve now traveled", 
            "dur": "3.45", 
            "start": "166.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "another half a meter.", 
            "dur": "2.63", 
            "start": "169.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Then you do that again, you\nhalve the distance again.", 
            "dur": "4.11", 
            "start": "172.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So now, your hands have traveled\n1/4 of a meter.", 
            "dur": "3.53", 
            "start": "176.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then it&#39;s an 1/8\nand 1/16 and 1/32.", 
            "dur": "6.91", 
            "start": "179.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then you keep doing\nthis forever, halving", 
            "dur": "2.42", 
            "start": "186.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the distance forever.", 
            "dur": "1.17", 
            "start": "189.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s say this does\nhave a value.", 
            "dur": "1.96", 
            "start": "190.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s give it a value.", 
            "dur": "0.98", 
            "start": "192.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s call it S--", 
            "dur": "1.505", 
            "start": "193.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "S for sum.", 
            "dur": "1.275", 
            "start": "194.795"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here&#39;s a trick that\nyou can do.", 
            "dur": "2.62", 
            "start": "196.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "First of all, I&#39;m going\nto multiply by 1/2.", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
            "start": "198.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m going to multiply the\nwhole thing by 1/2.", 
            "dur": "3.51", 
            "start": "201.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if I multiply the left hand\nside by 1/2, you get 1/2 of S.", 
            "dur": "6.62", 
            "start": "204.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "On the right hand side,\nI&#39;m going to multiply", 
            "dur": "1.9", 
            "start": "211.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "term by term by 1/2.", 
            "dur": "3.35", 
            "start": "213.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So 1 multiplied by 1/2 is 1/2.", 
            "dur": "3.5", 
            "start": "216.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m just going to write that\nthere-- going to leave a", 
            "dur": "2.222", 
            "start": "220.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "little gap.", 
            "dur": "1.358", 
            "start": "222.242"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, I&#39;m going to multiply\nthe 1/2 by 1/2,", 
            "dur": "2.8", 
            "start": "223.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which gives me 1/4.", 
            "dur": "2.21", 
            "start": "226.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I&#39;m doing it by term by\nterm, so 1/4 times 1/2 is 1/8,", 
            "dur": "4.86", 
            "start": "228.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and 1/8 by 1/2 is 1/16.", 
            "dur": "3.82", 
            "start": "233.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, I&#39;m going to subtract\nthose two things.", 
            "dur": "3.88", 
            "start": "237.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If I subtract, from the left,\nI get S minus 1/2 S, which", 
            "dur": "4.42", 
            "start": "241.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "gives you 1/2 S. On the right\nhand side, I&#39;m going to", 
            "dur": "5.59", 
            "start": "245.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "subtract these two lines.", 
            "dur": "1.65", 
            "start": "251.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I&#39;ve got 1.", 
            "dur": "1.54", 
            "start": "252.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I&#39;ve got plus 1/2 minus 1/2\nplus 1/4 minus 1/4 plus", 
            "dur": "4.8", 
            "start": "254.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "1/8 minus 1/8.", 
            "dur": "1.64", 
            "start": "259.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And all the terms cancel out.", 
            "dur": "2.22", 
            "start": "260.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So all you&#39;re left with is 1,\nwhich means, if everything&#39;s", 
            "dur": "5.53", 
            "start": "263.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "canceled out then, you can\nwork out what S is.", 
            "dur": "3.21", 
            "start": "268.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "S is equal to 2.", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "271.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this would be 2 meters.", 
            "dur": "2.82", 
            "start": "274.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So your hands would\ntravel 2 meters.", 
            "dur": "2.57", 
            "start": "277.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Even though it&#39;s an infinite\nprocess, your", 
            "dur": "2.63", 
            "start": "280.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hands do travel 2 meters.", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
            "start": "282.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, time is important,\nas well.", 
            "dur": "2.4", 
            "start": "285.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If each step was taking a\nsecond, then that&#39;s an", 
            "dur": "3.57", 
            "start": "287.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "infinite number of seconds,\nor if it was", 
            "dur": "1.74", 
            "start": "291.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "longer than a second.", 
            "dur": "1.6", 
            "start": "292.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So you would complete your\n2 meters, but it takes an", 
            "dur": "3.67", 
            "start": "294.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "infinite amount of time to\ncomplete your 2 meters.", 
            "dur": "2.6", 
            "start": "298.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So time is important as well.", 
            "dur": "2.16", 
            "start": "300.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So let&#39;s say we&#39;ll do it a\nlittle bit faster than that.", 
            "dur": "4.25", 
            "start": "302.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s say I move 1\nmeter per second.", 
            "dur": "3.12", 
            "start": "307.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I&#39;m going to move\n1 meter per second.", 
            "dur": "2.1", 
            "start": "310.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s the same, working out.", 
            "dur": "2.442", 
            "start": "312.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If I halve the distance, that\nwould take me 1 second.", 
            "dur": "3.658", 
            "start": "314.892"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then I halved the distance\nagain-- it would take me 1/2", 
            "dur": "2.15", 
            "start": "318.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "second, then 1/4 second.", 
            "dur": "2.46", 
            "start": "320.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I could travel 2 meters\nin 2 seconds.", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "323.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And my hands would clap.", 
            "dur": "1.38", 
            "start": "326.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So something like this-- an\ninfinite sum-- behaves well", 
            "dur": "3.87", 
            "start": "327.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when, if you take the sum and\nthen you keep adding one term", 
            "dur": "3.53", 
            "start": "331.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at a time, so you&#39;ve got lots\nof different sums getting", 
            "dur": "4.19", 
            "start": "334.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "closer and closer\nto your answer.", 
            "dur": "3.47", 
            "start": "339.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If that&#39;s the case, if\nyour partial sums--", 
            "dur": "4.38", 
            "start": "342.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that&#39;s what they&#39;re called-- are\ngetting closer and closer", 
            "dur": "3.4", 
            "start": "346.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to a value, then we say that&#39;s\na well-behaved sum, and at", 
            "dur": "5.83", 
            "start": "350.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "infinity, it is equal\nto it exactly.", 
            "dur": "4.06", 
            "start": "356.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it&#39;s not just getting closer\nand closer but not", 
            "dur": "2.46", 
            "start": "360.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "quite reaching.", 
            "dur": "1.78", 
            "start": "362.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is actually the whole\nthing properly.", 
            "dur": "3.24", 
            "start": "364.51"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it sounds like I&#39;m saying\nthat you can complete an", 
            "dur": "2.95", 
            "start": "367.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "infinite process.", 
            "dur": "1.37", 
            "start": "370.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, an infinite process doesn&#39;t\nhave a last step.", 
            "dur": "3.26", 
            "start": "372.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So how can something without\na last step be completed?", 
            "dur": "5.05", 
            "start": "375.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that&#39;s the paradox.", 
            "dur": "2.614", 
            "start": "380.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY HARAN: What is the--", 
            "dur": "1.096", 
            "start": "382.994"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and is there a solution?", 
            "dur": "1.22", 
            "start": "384.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "DR. JAMES GRIME: I have no easy\nanswers for you here.", 
            "dur": "4.24", 
            "start": "385.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is a paradox that has\nbaffled philosophers and", 
            "dur": "3.15", 
            "start": "389.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "mathematicians for\n2,500 years.", 
            "dur": "3.48", 
            "start": "392.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I wrestle with it as well.", 
            "dur": "2.105", 
            "start": "396.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There are greater minds than you\nand I that have wrestled", 
            "dur": "4.455", 
            "start": "398.285"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with this problem in the\nlast 2,500 years.", 
            "dur": "5.18", 
            "start": "402.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If this melts your brain,\ndon&#39;t worry.", 
            "dur": "2.51", 
            "start": "407.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You are in very good company.", 
            "dur": "2.89", 
            "start": "410.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY HARAN: Some of these\nnumbers where the digits", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "413.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "apparently go on forever\nand ever--", 
            "dur": "1.96", 
            "start": "415.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "pi, the square root of 2--", 
            "dur": "2.436", 
            "start": "417.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "how do they fit into all this?", 
            "dur": "1.934", 
            "start": "420.026"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "DR. JAMES GRIME: Yeah.", 
            "dur": "0.28", 
            "start": "421.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if something goes on forever,\nit&#39;s almost like", 
            "dur": "2.635", 
            "start": "422.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you&#39;re asking, can I even draw\nsomething with these decimal", 
            "dur": "4.475", 
            "start": "424.875"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "representations that\nnever finish?", 
            "dur": "2.71", 
            "start": "429.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it&#39;s the same sort of\nproblem that we&#39;ve got here.", 
            "dur": "2.805", 
            "start": "432.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But again, even though\nthat&#39;s an infinite", 
            "dur": "2.105", 
            "start": "434.865"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "process, it can be completed.", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "436.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I know that&#39;s bizarre.", 
            "dur": "0.86", 
            "start": "439.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But look.", 
            "dur": "1.24", 
            "start": "440.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If I draw a triangle, that has\nlength 1, that has length 1.", 
            "dur": "5.94", 
            "start": "442.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s a right angle.", 
            "dur": "1.41", 
            "start": "448.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this has length the\nsquare root of 2.", 
            "dur": "3.39", 
            "start": "449.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And there&#39;s no reason I can&#39;t\ndo that, even though the", 
            "dur": "2.4", 
            "start": "452.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "square root of 2 is irrational,\nwhich means the", 
            "dur": "2.46", 
            "start": "455.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "decimals go on forever.", 
            "dur": "2.43", 
            "start": "457.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Even though it&#39;s like that,\nthere&#39;s nothing stopping me", 
            "dur": "3.51", 
            "start": "460.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from drawing it.", 
            "dur": "1.51", 
            "start": "463.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the same way, there&#39;s nothing\nstopping me from", 
            "dur": "2.06", 
            "start": "465.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "clapping my hands.", 
            "dur": "1.84", 
            "start": "467.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can think of this as\nan infinite process.", 
            "dur": "2.77", 
            "start": "469.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m halving the distance an\ninfinite number of times.", 
            "dur": "3.82", 
            "start": "471.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But I can still clap my hands.", 
            "dur": "3.82", 
            "start": "475.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So these 19th century\nmathematicians had to work out", 
            "dur": "2.61", 
            "start": "479.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when these infinite sums behaved\nwell and when they", 
            "dur": "2.75", 
            "start": "482.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "behaved badly.", 
            "dur": "1.38", 
            "start": "484.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so there&#39;s a lot of\ntechnical detail behind that.", 
            "dur": "3.51", 
            "start": "486.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it just turned out to be\nrigorous and consistent, which", 
            "dur": "3.37", 
            "start": "489.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is very important.", 
            "dur": "2.2", 
            "start": "493.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But some of the tests that\nyou can use to prove that", 
            "dur": "3.84", 
            "start": "495.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "something is a well-behaved\nsum--", 
            "dur": "2.52", 
            "start": "499.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "well, they&#39;re quite easy.", 
            "dur": "1.02", 
            "start": "501.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;ll show you one.", 
            "dur": "1.15", 
            "start": "502.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What you can do is if you take\none of these terms--", 
            "dur": "4.66", 
            "start": "503.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m actually going\nto call it a.", 
            "dur": "1.806", 
            "start": "508.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You take one of them,\nthe nth term--", 
            "dur": "3.534", 
            "start": "510.246"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "an.", 
            "dur": "0.72", 
            "start": "513.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You divide that by the one that\ncame before it, and if", 
            "dur": "4.159", 
            "start": "514.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it&#39;s negative, well, you&#39;ll\nmake it positive, then.", 
            "dur": "3.571", 
            "start": "518.659"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you take those numbers--", 
            "dur": "1.929", 
            "start": "522.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if those numbers go\ntowards a value--", 
            "dur": "3.231", 
            "start": "524.159"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "let&#39;s call it r, as these\nn&#39;s get bigger.", 
            "dur": "5.39", 
            "start": "527.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If these numbers tend towards a\nvalue, and if that number is", 
            "dur": "4.49", 
            "start": "532.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "less than 1, then it&#39;s\nwell-behaved.", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
            "start": "537.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this was well-behaved.", 
            "dur": "2.1", 
            "start": "542.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Why was this well-behaved?", 
            "dur": "1.47", 
            "start": "544.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because if you take one of those\nterms and divide by the", 
            "dur": "3.44", 
            "start": "546.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "one that came before it,\nyou always get 1/2.", 
            "dur": "2.95", 
            "start": "549.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Look.", 
            "dur": "0.63", 
            "start": "552.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "1/2 divided by 1 is 1/2.", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "553.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "1/4 divided by 1/2\nis also 1/2.", 
            "dur": "3.05", 
            "start": "556.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These are all halves,\nactually.", 
            "dur": "1.67", 
            "start": "559.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You get a common\nfactor of 1/2--", 
            "dur": "2.71", 
            "start": "560.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "common ratio of 1/2\nfor each one.", 
            "dur": "2.96", 
            "start": "563.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That passes the test.", 
            "dur": "1.645", 
            "start": "566.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that&#39;s what this is.", 
            "dur": "0.965", 
            "start": "568.095"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is a test.", 
            "dur": "1.17", 
            "start": "569.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it passes the test.", 
            "dur": "0.86", 
            "start": "570.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is well-behaved.", 
            "dur": "1.38", 
            "start": "571.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If this was bigger than 1, then\nit&#39;s not well-behaved.", 
            "dur": "7.41", 
            "start": "572.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that could mean--", 
            "dur": "1.26", 
            "start": "579.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "well, it could mean it\ngoes on to infinity.", 
            "dur": "3.42", 
            "start": "581.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Or it could mean it&#39;s periodic\nor does something else weird.", 
            "dur": "3.19", 
            "start": "584.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it&#39;s not well-behaved.", 
            "dur": "1.88", 
            "start": "587.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the other case is if this\nnumber was equal to 1, we", 
            "dur": "4.42", 
            "start": "589.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "don&#39;t know.", 
            "dur": "1.52", 
            "start": "594.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It could be anything.", 
            "dur": "0.74", 
            "start": "595.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It could be either.", 
            "dur": "0.72", 
            "start": "596.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It could be well-behaved\nor not.", 
            "dur": "2.32", 
            "start": "597.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It depends.", 
            "dur": "1.05", 
            "start": "599.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So r equals to 1,\nwe&#39;re not sure.", 
            "dur": "2.642", 
            "start": "600.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY HARAN: What&#39;s a series\nwhere r is greater than 1?", 
            "dur": "3.768", 
            "start": "603.042"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Can you show me, what&#39;s a\nbadly behaved series?", 
            "dur": "2.65", 
            "start": "606.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "DR. JAMES GRIME: So if it was\nbigger than 1, than the terms", 
            "dur": "2.67", 
            "start": "609.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would be getting bigger and\nbigger and bigger each time,", 
            "dur": "2.91", 
            "start": "612.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "maybe not in a common\nratio way.", 
            "dur": "3.19", 
            "start": "615.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, we were talking about the", 
            "dur": "1.15", 
            "start": "618.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Fibonacci sequence earlier.", 
            "dur": "1.49", 
            "start": "619.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if we had something\nlike that, like 1", 
            "dur": "4.47", 
            "start": "620.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and 1 and 2 and 3.", 
            "dur": "3.17", 
            "start": "625.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you divide those, they don&#39;t\nhave a common ratio.", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "628.51"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But actually, the ratio\nis tending to", 
            "dur": "2.54", 
            "start": "631.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "1.618, the golden ratio.", 
            "dur": "3.16", 
            "start": "633.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So 1.618 would be\nbigger than 1.", 
            "dur": "2.18", 
            "start": "636.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this would be\nbadly behaved.", 
            "dur": "1.4", 
            "start": "639.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you added them together, you\nwould get a number that", 
            "dur": "2.65", 
            "start": "640.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "was going off to infinity\nin that case.", 
            "dur": "2.8", 
            "start": "643.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that would be called\ndivergent.", 
            "dur": "3.255", 
            "start": "645.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is well-behaved,\nour example.", 
            "dur": "1.77", 
            "start": "649.195"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it&#39;s called convergent.", 
            "dur": "2.165", 
            "start": "650.965"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "My question to physicists is if\nwe were literal about this", 
            "dur": "3.97", 
            "start": "653.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and considered the real world\nso that we are actually", 
            "dur": "4.53", 
            "start": "657.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "dividing a distance repeatedly\nin half over and over again", 
            "dur": "3.67", 
            "start": "661.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "infinitely many times, or\ndividing the time it takes to", 
            "dur": "4.09", 
            "start": "665.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "complete each step infinitely\nmany times so it&#39;s getting", 
            "dur": "3.39", 
            "start": "669.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "quicker, can you do that?", 
            "dur": "2.19", 
            "start": "672.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Can you divide space and time\ninfinitely many times?", 
            "dur": "5.2", 
            "start": "674.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I don&#39;t know the\nanswer to that.", 
            "dur": "1.62", 
            "start": "680.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I want a physicist\nto tell me.", 
            "dur": "3.28", 
            "start": "681.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We&#39;re in slightly the area of\ncalculus, as well, which some", 
            "dur": "4.04", 
            "start": "685.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of you may meet when you get\nhigher up at school.", 
            "dur": "4.04", 
            "start": "689.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Calculus helps you work out the\narea by adding up really", 
            "dur": "3.18", 
            "start": "693.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "thin strips together.", 
            "dur": "2.72", 
            "start": "696.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it&#39;s in the same area.", 
            "dur": "2.21", 
            "start": "699.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So Newton and Leibniz were\ntrying to add up areas by", 
            "dur": "4.65", 
            "start": "701.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "taking strips that were\nreally, really thin--", 
            "dur": "3.05", 
            "start": "705.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "not quite 0, but close to 0.", 
            "dur": "3.19", 
            "start": "708.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this idea was later replaced\nwith what we did", 
            "dur": "5.11", 
            "start": "712.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "here, the 19th century\nidea called limits.", 
            "dur": "3.85", 
            "start": "717.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this has taken a long\ntime to work out.", 
            "dur": "3.17", 
            "start": "721.11"
        }
